page.title: 03WOODLAND
page.content: Woodland. The area known as Carpenters Down Wood belongs to the Forestry Commission.It is made up of various named sections. These are 'copses', 'plantations', 'bushes'and 'pieces'. It is an area of mixed woodland , mainly coniferous but including some mature oak trees and other deciduous trees.There is a great deal of ground cover , much of it blackberry bushes.The plantations are separated by gravel walks and the whole area is rich in flora and fauna. In Basing Village there are about 1000 acres of land used as woodland or parkland.
